                                <emph>čerüvün</emph>, the equivalent of BHeb. <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">תִּפְלָה </foreign>
                            ‘wrong’, introduced with theHebrew phrase <foreign xml:lang="he"
                                style="unicode-bidi: embed;">או תאמר פשט ב׳ </foreign>
                            ‘or you will say a second interpretation’. | C: <emph>äbäslik</emph>. |
                            QB: <emph>äbäslik</emph>. | ADub.III.84: <emph>acuvun</emph>. |
                            Kobeckaitė (2019): <emph>ǯurumun</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-024-fn4" type="footnote">Hypercorrect form of
                                <emph>keče</emph>.</note>
                        <note xml:id="Job-024-fn5" type="footnote">JSul.I.04: <emph>kebek</emph>; a
                            scribal error.</note>
                    </app>
                </listApp>
